  "prompt": "What were Edwin Hubble works? How did he achieve them?",
  "response": "Edwin Hubble (1889-1953) was an American astronomer who made several groundbreaking contributions to our understanding of the universe:\n\n1. Expanding Universe Theory\n- Discovered that galaxies are moving away from each other\n- Developed the \"Hubble's Law\" which states that the speed of a galaxy's recession is proportional to its distance\n- Provided evidence for the Big Bang theory\n- Used spectroscopic measurements to calculate galaxy distances and velocities\n\n2. Galactic Classification\n- Created the \"Hubble Sequence\" for classifying galaxies\n- Categorized galaxies into different shapes: elliptical, spiral, and irregular\n- His classification system is still used by astronomers today\n\n3. Proving Existence of Galaxies Beyond Milky Way\n- Demonstrated that \"spiral nebulae\" were actually separate galaxies\n- Used the 100-inch Hooker Telescope at Mount Wilson Observatory\n- Observed Cepheid variable stars in Andromeda galaxy to calculate its distance\n- Proved galaxies existed outside our own Milky Way\n\n4. Astronomical Measurements\n- Developed precise methods for measuring astronomical distances\n- Used standard candle techniques like Cepheid variable stars\n- Improved understanding of cosmic scale and structure\n\nHubble's achievements transformed our understanding of the universe's size, structure, and evolution.",
